detaileddescription.para: Default constructor. Initializes vector with zeros.

Initializes vector by loading data from memory (via _mm256_lddq_si256).
init
Valid memory addres of minimal size of 256-bits (32 bytes).

Initializes vector with const value. Each cell will be set with value of init.
init
Value to be set.

Loads data from memory into vector (memory should be of size of at least 32 bytes). Memory doesn't need to be aligned to any specific boundary. If sP is nullptr this method has no effect.
sP
Pointer to memory from which to load data.

Saves vector data into an array.
dest
Destination array.

Saves data into given memory address. Memory doesn't need to be aligned to any specific boundary.
dest
A valid (non-nullptr) memory address with size of at least 32 bytes.

Saves data from vector into given memory address. Memory needs to be aligned on 32 byte boundary. See https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/docs/intrinsics-guide/index.html for more details.
dest
A valid (non-NULL) memory address aligned to 32-byte boundary.

New vector being a sum of this vector and bv.

New vector being a sum of this vector and b.

inbodydescription.para: Version giving correct answer everytime but no perf boost. __m128i result = _mm256_cvtpd_epi32( _mm256_round_pd( _mm256_div_pd( _mm256_cvtepi32_pd(_mm256_castsi256_si128(v)), _mm256_cvtepi32_pd(_mm256_castsi256_si128(bV.v)) ), _MM_FROUND_TO_ZERO |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC ) );
